 lively portrait of a unique community of performing artists, their intellectual ambitions and theatrical innovations, their business practices, and their fearless engagements with the politics and religion of their time.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aEnglish drama -- Early modern and Elizabethan, 1500-1600 -- History and criticism. 0aEnglish dramaxHistory and criticismxEarly modern and Elizabethan, 1500-1600. 0aEnglish dramayEarly modern and Elizabethan, 1500-1600xHistory and criticism. 0aLiterature and society -- England -- History -- 16th century. 0aLiterature and societyzEnglandxHistoryy16th century. 0aTheater -- England -- London -- History -- 16th century. 0aTheaterzEnglandzLondonxHistoryy16th century. 0aTheatrical companies -- England -- London -- History -- 16th century. 0aTheatrical companieszEnglandzLondonxHistoryy16th century. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Great Britain / General.2bisacsh1 aMacLean, Sally-Beth, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311067250340uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030020689040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300206890423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300206890/original  a978-3-11-067250-3  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles